# Eat and Drink Nearby

All of these restaurants are walking distance or a short drive from Rev Hall.

[Hawthorne Street Asylum](https://www.instagram.com/hawthorne_asylum/?hl=en) üå∂Ô∏è   
[1080 SE Madison St, Portland, OR 97214](https://maps.app.goo.gl/UMZyM2GncjRkiurX9) (13 min walk)  
the food cart pod that has it all. MASSIVE heated patios, a brand new bar, clean restrooms, and food to satisfy any craving and dietary requirement. It also has great sculptures and beautiful graffiti art, and a new foodcart truck made from an actual airplane.  

[Casa Vale](https://www.barcasavale.com/) üå∂Ô∏è:  
[215 SE 9th Ave Suite 109, Portland, OR 97214](https://maps.app.goo.gl/SiMqz2TiRgQNAsv99) (9 min walk)  
A cozy, wood-fired, Spanish-inspired restaurant, primarily tapas. There is a mostly enclosed, heated patio. It shares a building with [Scotch Lodge](https://www.scotchlodge.com/), a whiskey lounge (with a decent amount of non-alcoholic options), and [Paper Bridge](https://www.thepaperbridgepdx.com/), a Vietnamese Restaurant with a cozy, festive and soothing atmosphere.

[Worker‚Äôs Tap](https://workerstap.com/) üåà  
[101 SE 12th Ave, Portland, OR 97214](https://maps.app.goo.gl/T98KZiGc4d5j43g58) (8 min walk)  
A union, workers‚Äô-rights-themed cafe and bar, owned by its workers. Located in a converted Victorian-style home, the bar is downstairs and upstairs has board game rooms, and a library with books on mutual aid and historical BIPOC, queer and revolutionary figures. Food is available from a soul food restaurant they partner and share a patio with. Every Friday night is a trans and nonbinary social night at 8pm. Saturday night there is a union happy hour.

[Nong‚Äôs Khao Man Gai](https://khaomangai.com/)  
[609 SE Ankeny St C, Portland, OR 97214](https://maps.app.goo.gl/Ax4kgjMpRjdVNEsQA) (13 min walk)  
A long-standing foodcart that became too popular and they had to open their own restaurant. ‚ÄúKhao Man Gai means Chicken & Rice. It‚Äôs flavorful and well-balanced, served with Nong‚Äôs signature sauce and a side of soup.‚Äù Nong‚Äôs focuses on one main dish, but there are vegan options too. Buy some sauce to take home\!

[Afuri](https://afuri.us/)  
[923 SE 7th Ave, Portland, OR 97214](https://maps.app.goo.gl/am5c3hZN3SvpXMFb6) (13 min walk)  
One of Portland‚Äôs most popular ramen spots, with a focus on sustainability. Because it‚Äôs so popular, you may want to call ahead or reserve ahead of time.

[The Screen Door](https://screendoorrestaurant.com/)  
[2337 E Burnside St, Portland, OR 97214](https://maps.app.goo.gl/NBjUVNUxA6Yj1TYg6) (11 min walk)  
Another restaurant that‚Äôs been on the top of ‚Äúmust try when you visit Portland‚Äù lists for 2 decades, with large-portion comforting Southern style menu and desserts. This place is also very popular so you may want to call ahead of time.

[Le Pigeon](https://www.lepigeon.com/) [& Canard](https://www.canardrestaurant.com/)  
[738 E Burnside St, Portland, OR 97214](https://maps.app.goo.gl/e2MdjznYAPeQ4M2u5) (12 min walk)  
High end French restaurants that are paired together, also known for their wines and cocktails. It‚Äôs also recommended to have a reservation. Right next to Rontoms.

[Rontom‚Äôs](https://www.rontoms.net/) üå∂Ô∏è  
[600 E Burnside St, Portland, OR 97214](https://maps.app.goo.gl/Qpmk8dihFRnwr2KS9) (12 min walk)  
An old converted warehouse style bar with large open space with high ceilings and lots of places to lounge. It has a large heated patio with a ping pong table, and a large menu of craft cocktails and mocktails and comfort foods.

