# Uniquely Portland Experiences

## Unique Themed Restaurants, Bars & Clubs

[Raven‚Äôs Manor](https://www.ravensmanorexperience.com/)  
[235 SW 1st Ave, Portland, OR 97204](https://maps.app.goo.gl/EMoVVhsRCfTZQ96L6) (7 min drive/13 min transit)  
Portland‚Äôs Haunted Bar with bewitching, homemade craft cocktails, snacks and mocktails. Decor is classy yet spooky, with a terrifying attention to detail. You can also book an elixir-making experience in their ‚Äúlaboratory‚Äù \- classes available before and throughout the PyCascades weekend.

[Coffin Club](https://www.thecoffinclubpdx.com/about/)  
[421 SE Grand Ave, Portland, OR 97214](https://maps.app.goo.gl/xYekECngrLvFD9HY9) (11 min walk)  
Goth themed dance club, with a patio and vegan food truck. Most known for dance parties and goth music DJs and concerts. Feb 7th is their [‚ÄúSynth PNW Dark Elektro Music Fest‚Äù](https://www.treetix.com/event?id=203188&cal=coffinclub&append_refer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2F)

[Freeland Spirits](https://freelandspirits.com/) üåà  
[2671 NW Vaughn St, Portland, OR 97210](https://maps.app.goo.gl/dXEpUQAQ5EZsiWyB9)  
A women-owned bar and distillery, using ancient gin recipes and gin-aged bourbons. Although the atmosphere is very chill, there are often community fundraisers, drag shows, and other festive events.

[Sports Bra](https://thesportsbrapdx.com/) üåà  
[2512 NE Broadway, Portland, OR 97232](https://maps.app.goo.gl/X2FwW7pB7UxdeATS9)  
‚ÄúA must-visit, if not for its amazing menu, for the fact that it‚Äôs the nation‚Äôs first sports bar to exclusively show women‚Äôs sports. Chef and owner Jenny Nguyen created a menu based on traditional sports bar fare with nods to her Vietnamese upbringing. Packed with [vegan](https://www.travelportland.com/culture/vegan-food/) and [gluten-free](https://www.travelportland.com/culture/gluten-free-dining/) dining options, the drinks menu is equally inclusive, with great zero-proof drinks.

## Non-Alcoholic Drinks

Most bars in Portland (especially inner SE and NE) offer mocktails that are of equivalent quality to their alcoholic cocktails, but there are also several that specialize in non-alcoholic cocktails.

[List of the best rated mocktails in town](https://pdx.eater.com/maps/non-alcoholic-cocktails-mocktails-zero-proof-portland-bars-restaurants)

Many bars like [Sous√≥l](https://sousolbar.com/about) are founded by sober owners and have a zero-proof focus. A comprehensive [list here](https://www.travelportland.com/culture/mocktails/).

# In-Town Activities

## Self-Guided

[PDX SideWalk Joy Tour](https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1SvBvQ7RIB3k-gnshfvZfTM1rlqupmGw&ll=45.508020600000016%2C-122.61325710000001&z=15)  
All over Portland  
This also includes Tiny Library Tour, which includes libraries where you can trade seeds, mugs, dinosaurs, and more\!). You can also use the [Tiny Library World Map](https://littlefreelibrary.org/map/).

[Geocaching](https://www.geocaching.com/play):  
All over Portland.  
Portland has a lot of very specific, educational, funny and punny geograches.

# Shopping/Art, Neighborhood Centers

There are also a selection of cute shops and cafes up the street form Rontoms, Le Pigeon and the others on Burnside (10 min walk), such as [Oko vintage jewelry](https://okoportland.com/), [Dark Star Magick Shop](https://darkstarmagick.com/), [Coy and Co](https://coycopdx.com/) üåà plastic-free floral, and [Day Goods](https://www.daygoodspdx.com/) home furnishings.


# Short Drive outside Town

[McMenamin‚Äôs Edgefield](https://www.mcmenamins.com/edgefield)  
[2126 SW Halsey St, Troutdale, OR 97060](https://maps.app.goo.gl/Kq4o92rk7vJ8dwnh8) (25 min drive \- near SugarPine)

Massive space with 9 restaurants/bars, movie theater, concert venue, a small and not-stuffy golf course, and one of our favorite large, heated, tropical soaking pools that has its own bar, spa and teahouse.   

[Sugarpine Drive In](https://sugarpinedrivein.com/)  
[1208 E Historic Columbia River Hwy, Troutdale, OR 97060](https://maps.app.goo.gl/S7hUuUBAVQMREbvm6) (25 min drive)

Adorable 50s style drive in diner on the Sandy river. If you‚Äôre up for an adventure, you can hike down to the river and walk along the beach or along nearby trails.   
